result.execSummary:
The defendant Billy Joe Snyder was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

08:36 AM Defendant Billy Joe Snyder in court with attorney Mark Drew Biller.  Defendant in custody.   Joseph Schieffer, District Attorney, appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Case on for Sentencing Hearing.  DA advises State is in compliance with victim's rights.  Mr. Biller recites plea agreement:  15 CF 43-plead to count 1 Poss of Meth, Count 2 fel bail jump.  15 CF 45 dismissed outright.  15 CF 05 dismissed outright  All other counts and files were DRI for sentencing and restitution purposes.  Parties agree on jail credit of 217 days combined.  State acknowledges receipt of PSI, no changes.  Mr. Biller acknowledges receipt of PSI, no changes.  15 CF 45 is dismissed but the VIS was reviewed by Court and previously parties indicated the $1000 bond posted was to be applied to restitution in that dismissed case.   Parties are in agreement with that.  Mr. Schieffer makes argument - requests Court go along with recommendation in PSI.  Probation with a withheld sentence.  No VIS to provide to Court in 15 CF 43.  Mr. Biller makes argument for probation.  Mr. Biller has exhibits 1 (programs completed in jail) and 2 (assessment) marked.  No objection to the Court receiving exhibits by State.  Court receives the exhibits.  Mr. Snyder makes statement to the Court.  Court reviews sentencing considerations.  Court advises Mr. Snyder that as he is a convicted felony he can possess no firearms for life.  Court finds Mr. Snyder is eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Progarm and Substance Abuse Program.  Court orders:  Count 1 - Possession of Meth - Sentence of 1 year in County Jail imposed & stayed, probation for 4 years.  Credit for 217 days.  Court costs - $290.60  plus $250 DNA surcharge,  payable to COC within 60 days unless payment plan is completed.  If not paid within 60 days, warrant can be issued.  Conditions:  any conditions recommended by agent, absolute sobriety, comply with AODA and Rule 25 assessment, successfully complete treatment at River Place in Anoka, report to probation today, cooperate and complete any treatment program DOC deems necessary, once completed treatment program and any inpatient, that he maintain full-time employment or full time student as college attendee.  Count 2 - Felony bail jumping, w/h sentence, Probation 4 years - concurrent to Count 1.  Court costs $540.60 for Count 2.  All conditions of probation for Count 1 apply to Count 2 as well.  Re: Count 2, possibility of 6 years in prison if he gets revoked.  Appeal rights provided.  $1000 restitution in 15 CF 45 to be paid to the victim.  DNA to be provided to the Sheriff's Dept. before leaving.
Mod. of bond denied.

01:36 PM Defendant, Billy Joe Snyder, appeared in person, in custody, with Attorney Mark Biller, by phone.  Atty. Joseph Schieffer appeared on behalf of State of Wisconsin.  Case on for a Bail Hearing.  Mr. Schieffer believes case is awaiting sentencing.  Requests to revoke bond, not entitled to bond as he has already pled.  Mr. Biller asks for signature bond, having trouble getting date set for sentencing.  Court asks why he did not appear on 1/28?  He was incarcerated in MN.  Court advises Mr. Snyder was already found guilty, release after conviction is at discretion of court and Court exercises discretion and denies release and bond/bail is revoked and he shall remain in custody.  Sentencing should be set with Judge Tolan.  Mr. Biller argues further.  Court advises he will need to discuss with Judge Tolan.  Mr. Snyder makes a statement, attorney advises him not to.  He missed his court date only because he was incarcerated somewhere else.  Court is adjourned.

Defendant, Billy Joe Snyder, appeared with Attorney Mark Drew Biller.  Attorney Daniel Steffen appeared for the State. Plq filed. Atty Biller resites agreement, Def. to plead to counts 1 & 2 in case 2015CF43, cases 15CF45 and 16CF5 are dismissed outright, all others are DRI. PSI to be ordered The State provides reasons  for reaching this agreement. In Count 1 in 2015CF45 the State moves to amend to misd. theft 943.20 and dismissed, the restitution of $1,000 to be read in, amount stip to.  The Court examines Def. re the PLQ, witness ID's, it is his signature on it. Constitutional rights being waived are spelled out. Def. agrees.  Being convicted of a FE explained to Def. He understands the elements of the 2 charges he is pleading to. Def. has no questions. The Court explains read in charges. The Court explains the difference between a withheld sentence as opposed to an imposed/stayed. No threats or promises made to him to plead today. He has had enough time to talk w/his attorney about the pleadins. Def. enters pleas of G to counts 1 & 2. Pleas entered FKV and I. understands  the nature and understanding of the penalties of the 2 charges. The Court finds him G. No longer can use or possess a fire arm. 15CF45 as amended, read in for restitution and dismissed outright as is 16CF5. All TR's and FO are dismissed. and all other CM's, CF's, and CT are DRI.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 28, 2019 at 11:00 am. Modification of bond denied @ this time. Back on the record 9:43, the Court orders the $1,000 restitution, to be paid out of bond and the balance refunded.
